{{Short description|Painting by Childe Hassam}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file=File:Coast Scene, Isles of Shoals MET DT5583.jpg | caption= | alt= |image_size = | title=Coast Scene, Isles of Shoals | other_language_1= | other_title_1= | other_title_2= | artist=[[Childe Hassam]] | subject= | year=1901 | material=Oil on canvas | height_metric = 63.2 | width_metric = 76.5 | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | city=[[New York City]] | museum=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] | accession=09.72.6 }}
'''''Coast Scene, Isles of Shoals''''' is a 1901 painting by [[Childe Hassam]] which is in the collection of the [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/11032?sortBy=Relevance&amp;ft=Childe+Hassam&amp;offset=0&amp;rpp=100&amp;pos=61|title=www.metmuseum.org|website=www.metmuseum.org|access-date=2018-08-05}}</ref>
Done in oil on canvas in luminous colours, the painting depicts the remote Isles of Shoals off the rocky shoreline of [[New England]], a favourite haunt of Childe Hassam at the end of the 19th century and where he painted a series of similar coastal scenes.
The painting is accompanied at the Metropolitan Museum of Art by ''[[Surf, Isles of Shoals]]'', a similar work by Hassam.
The work is currently (2018) not on view.
