{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Sandro Botticelli 016.jpg | title=Lamentation over the Dead Christ | artist=Sandro Botticelli | year=1490–1492 | medium=Tempera on panel | height_metric=140 | width_metric=207 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | museum=Alte Pinakothek | city=Munich }} The '''''Lamentation over the Dead Christ''''', is a painting of the common subject of the [[Lamentation of Christ]] by the [[Italian Renaissance]] master [[Sandro Botticelli]], finished around 1490-1492. It is now in the [[Alte Pinakothek]], in [[Munich]].
The portrait shows the inert body of [[Jesus Christ|Christ]] surrounded by the [[Virgin Mary|Virgin]], [[St. Peter]], and [[Mary Magdalene]], [[St. John the Evangelist]], [[St. Jerome]] and [[St. Paul]].
The pathetic expressions of the characters were a novelty in Botticelli's art: under the spiritual influence of [[Savonarola]]'s preachings in [[Florence]], which began around the time the work was executed, he started in fact to abandon the allegoric inspiration that had made him a favourite of the Medici court in favour of more intimate and painstaking religious reflection.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artonline.it/opera.asp?IDOpera=48 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-06-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930160530/http://www.artonline.it/opera.asp?IDOpera=48 |archivedate=2007-09-30 |df= }}</ref>
==See also== * [[Lamentation over the Dead Christ (Botticelli, Milan)|''Lamentation over the Dead Christ'']] in Milan.
